        #     "body": "{\"id\": \"123\", \"metadata\": \"{\\\"caseId\\\": \\\"2\\\", \\\"userId\\\": \\\"1\\\", \\\"documentType\\\": \\\"personal_statement\\\", \\\"language\\\": \\\"English\\\", \\\"personalStatement\\\": \\\"Dear Immigration Officer,\\\\n\\\\nMy name is XXX, and I was born in a small city in China. Due to my religious beliefs and political views, my family and I have lived under government oppression and surveillance. From a young age, I was taught to be cautious with my words and actions, as any careless remark could lead to severe consequences. I have witnessed family members and friends face unjust treatment because of their beliefs and opinions, which has heightened my yearning for freedom and human rights.\\\\n\\\\nIn China, my religious beliefs and political views have made me a target for the authorities. I have been unjustly detained and interrogated multiple times, enduring physical and psychological abuse. Despite this, I have steadfastly adhered to my beliefs and principles, deeply convinced of the importance of freedom and human rights. To seek freedom and safety, I had to leave my homeland and come to this country full of hope and opportunity.\\\\n\\\\nIn the city where I lived, expressing dissent or holding different political beliefs is extremely dangerous. I have seen many friends and relatives arrested, detained, or even disappeared for voicing their opinions. I know that if I stayed in China, I would face even more severe persecution and possibly lose my life. To protect myself and my family, I chose to flee this dangerous and oppressive environment.\\\\n\\\\nAfter arriving in this new country, I have felt an unprecedented sense of freedom and safety. Here, I can freely express my views and beliefs without fear of surveillance or persecution. This freedom is invaluable to me as it allows me to live authentically and pursue my dreams. However, I also understand that as an asylum seeker, I need to obtain legal status to truly begin my new life.\\\\n\\\\nI earnestly request that your government understand my situation and grant me the opportunity for asylum. For me, this is not just a new beginning, but also a hope to live in freedom and dignity. I will strive to integrate into this society and contribute to the prosperity and development of this country. Thank you for your attention and understanding of my application.\\\", \\\"personalStatementInOriginalLanguage\\\": \\\"尊敬的移民局官员：\\\\n\\\\n我名叫XXX，出生于中国的一个小城市。由于我的宗教信仰和政治观点，我和我的家人一直生活在政府的压迫和监视之下。从小，我就被教导要谨慎言行，因为任何不慎的言论都有可能招致严重的后果。我多次目睹家人和朋友因为他们的信仰和意见而遭受不公正的待遇，这使我对自由和人权的渴望变得尤为强烈。\\\\n\\\\n在中国，我的宗教信仰和政治观点使我成为当局的眼中钉。我曾多次被无理拘留和审问，经历了身体和心理上的虐待。尽管如此，我仍然坚定地坚持我的信仰和立场，因为我深信自由和人权的重要性。为了寻求自由和安全，我不得不离开我的家乡，来到这个充满希望和机会的国家。\\\\n\\\\n在我生活的城市，表达异议或拥有不同的政治信仰是非常危险的。我目睹了许多朋友和亲人因为发表不同意见而被逮捕、关押，甚至失踪。我深知如果继续留在中国，我将面临更严重的迫害，甚至失去生命。为了保护自己和家人，我选择了逃离这个充满危险和压迫的环境。\\\\n\\\\n来到这个新国家后，我感受到了前所未有的自由和安全。在这里，我可以自由地表达我的观点和信仰，不必担心被监视或迫害。这种自由对我来说是无比珍贵的，因为它让我能够以真实的自己生活和追求梦想。然而，我也知道，作为一名寻求庇护者，我需要获得合法的身份才能真正开始新的生活。\\\\n\\\\n我恳请贵国政府能够理解我的处境，并给予我庇护的机会。对于我来说，这不仅仅是一个新的开始，更是一个能让我在自由和尊严中生活的希望。我将努力融入这个社会，为这个国家的繁荣和发展贡献我的力量。感谢您对我申请的关注和理解。\\\", \\\"client\\\": {\\\"lastName\\\": \\\"Hai\\\", \\\"firstName\\\": \\\"Yafei\\\", \\\"gender\\\": \\\"Male\\\", \\\"alienNumber\\\": \\\"A245-846-729\\\"}, \\\"attorney\\\": {\\\"firstName\\\": \\\"Wenyao\\\", \\\"lastName\\\": \\\"Yang\\\", \\\"companyName\\\": \\\"Concord & Sage PC\\\", \\\"attorneyBarNo\\\": \\\"348833\\\", \\\"phone\\\": \\\"626 766 9272\\\", \\\"email\\\": \\\"yangwenyao@concordsage.com\\\", \\\"address\\\": \\\"1360 Valley Vista Dr., Suite 140\\\", \\\"city\\\": \\\"Diamond Bar\\\", \\\"state\\\": \\\"CA\\\", \\\"zip\\\": \\\"91765\\\"}, \\\"caseInfo\\\": {\\\"courtAddress\\\": \\\"100 MONTGOMERY ST., SUITE 800\\\", \\\"courtCity\\\": \\\"SAN FRANCISCO\\\", \\\"courtState\\\": \\\"CA\\\", \\\"courtZip\\\": \\\"94104\\\", \\\"judgeName\\\": \\\"Savage, Patrick S.\\\", \\\"hearingDate\\\": \\\"October 14, 2025\\\", \\\"hearingTime\\\": \\\"1:30 PM\\\"}}\"}"
