        #     "body": "{\"id\": \"123\", \"metadata\": \"{\\\"documentName\\\": \\\"eoir_proofofservice_for_i589_form\\\", \\\"documentType\\\": \\\"eoir_proofofservice\\\", \\\"document\\\": \\\"I-589 Form\\\", \\\"caseId\\\": \\\"242\\\", \\\"userId\\\": \\\"10\\\", \\\"client\\\": {\\\"lastName\\\": \\\"Yang\\\", \\\"firstName\\\": \\\"Zhao\\\", \\\"dateOfBirth\\\": \\\"09/03/1985\\\", \\\"countryOfOrigin\\\": \\\"China\\\", \\\"gender\\\": \\\"Female\\\", \\\"residential_address\\\": \\\"1 Shore Lane APT1510 Jersey City, US-0-NJ 07310\\\", \\\"alienNumber\\\": \\\"64819471111\\\", \\\"additionalApplicants\\\": \\\"\\\", \\\"additionalApplicantAlienNumber\\\": \\\"111111-111, 22-222-22332\\\", \\\"personalStatement\\\": \\\"My name is Zhao Yang, holding a Chinese passport with the number SE0000000, female, born in Chenghua, Guangdong, China on September 3, 1985, and I am 39 years old this year. I entered the United States from recent entry location on July 11, 2024, under the status of B1. I have a fluency in English and also speak Japanese.\\\\n\\\\nI arrived in the U.S. seeking asylum based on religious and national origin persecution. My escape from Pingdingshan City, Henan Province, China, was provoked by the removal of religious and cultural symbols from my residence by local authorities on November 19, 2019. This oppressive act underscored the bigotry and intolerance I faced due to my faith and background. The escalating threat of continued mistreatment and potential arrest prompted my immediate departure to the U.S.\\\\n\\\\nThe grim reality of persecution in my home country leaves me no choice but to seek refuge here. The heinous actions of the authorities only foreshadow the grave danger awaiting me if I were to return. The torment and discrimination I endured in China have stripped me of safety and freedom. The urgency of my plea for asylum rests upon the stark certainty of relentless persecution upon my return.\\\"}, \\\"attorney\\\": {\\\"lastName\\\": \\\"li\\\", \\\"firstName\\\": \\\"qin\\\", \\\"companyName\\\": \\\"Concord Sage PC\\\", \\\"attorneyBarNo\\\": \\\"349218\\\", \\\"attorneyBarState\\\": \\\"CA\\\", \\\"phone\\\": \\\"6197326858\\\", \\\"email\\\": \\\"liqin66@concordsage.com\\\", \\\"address\\\": \\\"209 1360 VALLEY VISTA DR\\\", \\\"city\\\": \\\"DIAMOND BAR\\\", \\\"state\\\": \\\"CA\\\", \\\"zip\\\": \\\"91765\\\"}, \\\"caseInfo\\\": {\\\"courtAddress\\\": \\\"1234 Main St, New York, NY 10001\\\", \\\"courtCity\\\": \\\"New York\\\", \\\"courtState\\\": \\\"NY\\\", \\\"courtZip\\\": \\\"10001\\\", \\\"judgeName\\\": \\\"Judge john doE\\\", \\\"hearingDate\\\": \\\"12/31/2022\\\", \\\"hearingTime\\\": \\\"9:00 AM\\\"}, \\\"documents\\\": [\\\"Ex.1 Attorney Cover Letter\\\", \\\"Ex.2 Form G-28\\\", \\\"Ex.3 1-589\\\"], \\\"shipping_method\\\": \\\"USPS\\\", \\\"personalStatement\\\": \\\"My name is Zhao Yang, holding a Chinese passport with the number SE0000000, female, born in Chenghua, Guangdong, China on September 3, 1985, and I am 39 years old this year. I entered the United States from recent entry location on July 11, 2024, under the status of B1. I have a fluency in English and also speak Japanese.\\\\n\\\\nI arrived in the U.S. seeking asylum based on religious and national origin persecution. My escape from Pingdingshan City, Henan Province, China, was provoked by the removal of religious and cultural symbols from my residence by local authorities on November 19, 2019. This oppressive act underscored the bigotry and intolerance I faced due to my faith and background. The escalating threat of continued mistreatment and potential arrest prompted my immediate departure to the U.S.\\\\n\\\\nThe grim reality of persecution in my home country leaves me no choice but to seek refuge here. The heinous actions of the authorities only foreshadow the grave danger awaiting me if I were to return. The torment and discrimination I endured in China have stripped me of safety and freedom. The urgency of my plea for asylum rests upon the stark certainty of relentless persecution upon my return.\\\", \\\"personalStatementInOriginalLanguage\\\": \\\"我叫赵阳，持有中国护照，编号为SE0000000，女性，出生于1985年9月3日，今年38岁。我于2024年7月11日从最近的一个地点进入美国。在那之前，我于2024年7月3日从另一个地点入境。\\\\n\\\\n我至今未婚，没有子女。目前，我最关心的是基于宗教和国籍原因寻求避难，因为我在祖国中国遭受迫害。我遭遇的虐待发生在2019年11月19日，当时来自河南省平顶山市湛河区警察局的警察来到我在湛河区后城村的家中。他们要求移除我们住所外展示的用阿拉伯字母书写的对联和画有回族传统主题的装饰画。尽管我提出反对，但警察们还是拆下了这些物品，称之为阿拉伯文本令他们感到不适。他们用标有“民族团结”字样的海报替换了一些装饰，并警告我们，如果我们重新悬挂阿拉伯文本的展示物，将会面临未来的检查和潜在的逮捕。\\\\n\\\\n这一事件深深困扰了我的家庭，展示了对我们文化表达和传统的根本误解和限制。当局的行动显示了对多样性和文化实践的缺乏包容心，给我们的家庭灌输了恐惧和不确定性。\\\\n\\\\n我对回到中国感到恐惧，因为那里的压迫环境限制了宗教和文化的自由。我家中发生的事件突显了在中国对宗教和少数民族的持续迫害和打压，让我对如果返回将面临的后果感到真正恐惧和忧虑。\\\\n\\\\n我没有任何组织可以保证我返国后的安全或保护。当局加剧了对我的关注，持续对我进行监视，加重了我对自己和家人安全和福祉的担忧。因此，我感到有必要在美国寻求避难，以确保未来我可以自由地信仰并表达文化身份，不用担心遭受迫害或压迫。\\\", \\\"taskId\\\": \\\"530\\\"}\"}"
